review_blob: A multifaceted flavor, but almost overly malty with little sweetness to balance. Poured with more head than am used too, which may have diminished the taste a bit.
This was a very unique wheat ale with flavors similar to those of an English IPA combined with strong vanilla undertones. Clarity was good, aroma pleasing, and poured with minimal head.
This ale looked and smelled like a trippel, but its flavor was harsh and what few decent notes it possessed passed quickly.
beer_name: Thirsty Dog Bourbon Barrel Aged Cerberus

review_blob: One of the most well balanced IPAs available.  Smooth yet complex flavors with a cleaner finish compared to many others.
Good appearance and aroma,  but spices are unbalanced and give this IPA an overly bitter after flavor.
A nice thick stout with a smooth flavor, but one that bites back harder than one should.

What can I say, everything about this Triple is perfection.  Light head, multiple layers of flavor, beautiful appearance, sweet aftertastes, everything I want in an ale.  Be forewarned, however, it does not travel well if not maintained at the proper temperature (I prefer mine at ~10C, any colder and the flavor is ruined).
If I could rate this "brew" a zero, I certainly would.  Worst tasting, foulest smelling, most remorseful purchase of a beer Ive ever made.  Id have rather done a shot of rubbing alcohol.
